<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-approximation-and-errors" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Approximation and Errors</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      Measurements are never perfectly exact because instruments can only measure to a certain degree of accuracy. This limitation creates an absolute error, which measures how far a recorded value may differ from the working value.
    </p>
  </introduction>
